<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-30T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="88" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W./5–2545: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-30T13:00:00-04:00">June 30,
                                1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1016. Concerning proposed establishment safety zone Shanghai (Deptel 585
                        April 16) Dept informing Swiss and Swedish missions <pb facs="0135" n="125" xml:id="pg_125"/> here<note n="55" xml:id="d88fn55">By memoranda to the
                            Swedish and Swiss Legations, dated June 30, not printed.</note> that
                        proposal has been considered by U S military authorities and suggestion is
                        one to which U S govt cannot accede.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>